OL,6,FAn NSPCC spokesperson said: "This is a
OL,7,Fprofoundly sad case. Zahra was
OL,8,Fentrusted into the care of Gholami,
OL,9,Fafter her mother died when she was
OL,10,Fborn. But instead of treating her with
OL,11,Flove and care, he violently abused
OL,12,Fher, taking her life.
OL,14,F"Very young children are particularly
OL,15,Fvulnerable to abuse because they are
OL,16,Fcompletely reliant on the adults
OL,17,Faround them for care and protection.
OL,18,F'Bright' and 'curious' little Zahra
OL,19,Fwas devastatingly let down by those
OL,20,Fwho had promised to take care of her.
